  "prompt": "How do I get person online status when he is on whatsapp call?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, WhatsApp does have mechanisms for indicating when someone is online, including when they are on a call. However, WhatsApp does not provide a public API or direct method for third-party apps to check the status of someone's online presence or whether they are on a call specifically.\n\nHere are a few ways you might determine if someone is online or on a call:\n\n1. **Manual Check**: You can open WhatsApp and check the contact's status directly in the chat or contact list. If someone is online, WhatsApp typically shows \"online\" under their name. If they are on a call, it might show \"on a call\".\n\n2. **Messaging**: If you send a message to the person, you might not get a reply immediately if they are on a call. \n\n3. **Last Seen**: WhatsApp shows the last time a person was online. If their \"Last Seen\" is very recent, and they are not showing up as online now, they might be on another call.\n\nPlease note that these methods are limited to manual checking and depend on the privacy settings of the user's account. Many users opt to hide their \"Last Seen\" status, and WhatsApp has strict privacy policies around user data. \n\nIf you need more fine-grained control or automatic checks, there currently isn\u2019t a public API provided by WhatsApp for such purposes due to privacy concerns. \n\nIt's also worth noting that using unauthorized scripts or third-party apps to track someone's online status can violate WhatsApp's terms of service and even applicable laws on privacy. Always respect individual privacy and use such information responsibly.",
